as a result of the influx of appeals , the death penalty effectively ceased to exist in the united states for the remainder of the 1960s and 1970s , and the supreme court considered the issue in the 1972 case of furman v. georgia , where the justices , in a 5 to 4 decision , effectively suspended the death penalty laws of states across the country on the ground of the capricious imposition of the penalty .

